sql_query.sql: SELECT 1 AS one FROM "oauth_access_tokens" WHERE "oauth_access_tokens"."token" = $1 AND "oauth_access_tokens"."id" != $2 LIMIT $3
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "users" WHERE "users"."email" = $1 AND "users"."id" != $2 LIMIT $3
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "email_domain_blocks" WHERE "email_domain_blocks"."domain" IN ($1, $2) LIMIT $3
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "canonical_email_blocks" WHERE "canonical_email_blocks"."canonical_email_hash" = $1 LIMIT $2

metadata.name: Confirmations POST /api/v1/emails/confirmations with an oauth token when user was created by the same application with email param updates the user's e-mail address
